---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Fundamentals 5 — Lisa Rae"
  description="Unfolding case study: Patient Safety — Falls & Pressure Injury Prevention (FUN-05)"
>

  <div class="breadcrumb">
    <a href={base}>Home</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <a href={`${base}cases/`}>Cases</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <a href={`${base}cases/fundamentals/`}>Fundamentals</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <span>Fundamentals 5 — Lisa Rae</span>
  </div>

  <!-- ── CASE HEADER ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="case-header">
    <span class="card-tag">Patient Safety</span>
    <h1>Fundamentals 5 — Lisa Rae</h1>
    <p class="case-subtitle">Falls &amp; Pressure Injury Prevention in an Older Adult</p>
    <div class="case-meta">
      <span>👤 Lisa Rae, 78 years, White Female</span>
      <span>⏱ Scenario: 20 – 30 minutes</span>
      <span>💬 Debrief: 20 – 30 minutes</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── HOW TO USE ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="callout callout-info">
    <strong>📖 How to Use This Unfolding Case Study</strong>
    <p>Work through each phase in order. Information is revealed progressively — exactly as it would be in a real clinical encounter. Before reading each answer, pause and reason through the question yourself. Use the <strong>▶ Reveal Answer</strong> toggles to check your thinking.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       PHASE 1 — YOU ARRIVE AT THE BEDSIDE
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="phase-card" id="phase1">
    <div class="phase-header">
      <span class="phase-badge">Phase 1</span>
      <h2>You Arrive at the Bedside</h2>
    </div>

    <p class="phase-intro">
      You are the day-shift nurse on a medical-surgical unit. You receive handoff report on a patient admitted overnight and head to perform your initial assessment.
    </p>

    <div class="info-grid">
      <div class="info-block">
        <h3>📋 Handoff Report</h3>
        <table class="data-table">
          <tbody>
            <tr><th>Patient</th><td>Lisa Rae</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Age / DOB</th><td>78 years old</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Gender / Race</th><td>Female · White</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Admission Dx</th><td>Mechanical fall; hypotension</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Allergy</th><td>NKDA</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Code Status</th><td>Full code</td></tr>
            <tr><th>PMH</th><td>Hypertension, Type 2 DM (diet-controlled), osteoporosis, urinary incontinence, prior fall 3 months ago</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div class="info-block">
        <h3>💊 Current Medications (on MAR)</h3>
        <ul class="med-list">
          <li>0.9% Normal Saline IV at 75 mL/hr</li>
          <li>Hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ) 25 mg PO daily — <span class="badge-warning">HOLD today per order</span></li>
          <li>Hydromorphone 0.5 mg IV q4h PRN pain (right hip)</li>
          <li>Acetaminophen 650 mg PO q6h scheduled</li>
          <li>Calcium carbonate 600 mg + Vitamin D 400 IU PO BID</li>
          <li>Metformin 500 mg PO daily with evening meal</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="scene-box">
      <h3>🚪 Entering the Room — What You Observe</h3>
      <p>
        Ms. Rae is a 78-year-old woman lying in a hospital bed, appearing pale and slightly uncomfortable. She is awake and alert, oriented to person, place, and time. The bed is in a semi-elevated position. You notice the call light is not within reach. A Foley catheter bag is hanging on the bed frame below the level of the mattress. The path between the bed and the bathroom is partially obstructed by a meal tray table.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3>🔒 SWIPE Safety Assessment</h3>
    <p>Before touching the patient, perform your environmental safety check:</p>
    <table class="data-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Letter</th><th>Check</th><th>What You Find</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>S</strong></td><td>Siderails up</td><td>Only 1 rail up — <span class="text-danger">needs correction</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>W</strong></td><td>Wristband on, matches chart</td><td>Present and correct — two identifiers confirmed</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>I</strong></td><td>IV lines — site, patency, rate, label</td><td>Left forearm peripheral IV; site without redness; NS infusing at 75 mL/hr</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>P</strong></td><td>Pull cord / call light within reach</td><td><span class="text-danger">Out of reach — needs correction</span></td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>E</strong></td><td>Equipment — bed position, socks, path clear</td><td>Bed elevated; no non-skid socks on patient; path partially blocked by tray table; <span class="badge-warning">FALL RISK</span> band on wrist</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <details class="reveal-block">
      <summary>▶ Clinical Reasoning: What safety corrections do you make immediately before beginning your assessment?</summary>
      <div class="reveal-content">
        <p><strong>Immediate safety corrections (before any other action):</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Raise all appropriate siderails (2–3 rails, per facility policy)</li>
          <li>Lower the bed to its lowest position</li>
          <li>Place call light within easy reach — demonstrate use to Ms. Rae</li>
          <li>Apply non-skid socks</li>
          <li>Post fall-risk sign on door and above bed</li>
          <li>Clear the path between bed and bathroom; reposition tray table against wall</li>
          <li>Ensure Foley catheter tubing is not looped on the floor (trip hazard) and bag is secured below bladder level</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Why these corrections matter:</strong> Ms. Rae is already admitted for a fall. Her hypotension and right hip pain put her at extreme risk for a second fall during hospitalization. Every environmental modification reduces that risk before any formal nursing intervention begins.</p>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>

  <!-- connector -->
  <div class="phase-connector">⬇ As you complete your safety sweep, Ms. Rae begins sharing what happened at home…</div>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       PHASE 2 — HISTORY & MEDICATION CAUSE CHAIN
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="phase-card" id="phase2">
    <div class="phase-header">
      <span class="phase-badge">Phase 2</span>
      <h2>History &amp; Medication Cause Chain</h2>
    </div>

    <p class="phase-intro">
      You sit with Ms. Rae and gather a focused history. She is alert and cooperative, though slightly anxious about being in the hospital.
    </p>

    <div class="info-grid">
      <div class="info-block">
        <h3>🗣 History from Ms. Rae</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Lives alone in a single-story home; uses a <strong>cane</strong> for ambulation since a fall 3 months ago</li>
          <li>This morning she got up from bed to use the bathroom and felt <strong>"very dizzy and lightheaded"</strong></li>
          <li>Lost her balance in the hallway and fell, landing on her right side</li>
          <li>She denies hitting her head; denies loss of consciousness</li>
          <li>When asked about her medications, she pauses: <em>"Oh no — I think I took my water pill twice this morning. I forgot I'd already taken it."</em></li>
          <li>Has been on HCTZ for 3 years; this is the first time she has doubled the dose</li>
          <li>Reports her urine has been "very pale and a lot" since the double dose this morning</li>
          <li>Prior fall 3 months ago was also related to dizziness when getting up quickly</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="info-block">
        <h3>⚠️ Medication Alert — HCTZ Double Dose</h3>
        <div class="callout callout-danger">
          <p><strong>Hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ) 25 mg</strong> is a thiazide diuretic used to treat hypertension. A double dose causes:</p>
          <ul style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">
            <li>Excessive urinary output → rapid volume depletion</li>
            <li>Decreased intravascular volume → low blood pressure</li>
            <li>Orthostatic hypotension — worst when changing position (lying → sitting → standing)</li>
            <li>Electrolyte losses: hypokalemia (low K⁺), hyponatremia (low Na⁺)</li>
            <li>Risk of falls, syncope, and acute kidney injury in the elderly</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3>🔗 The Cause Chain — Connecting the Dots</h3>
    <div class="chain-flow">
      <div class="chain-step chain-step-drug">
        <span class="chain-icon">💊</span>
        <strong>HCTZ 25 mg × 2 (double dose)</strong>
        <small>Thiazide diuretic — accidentally doubled this morning</small>
      </div>
      <div class="chain-arrow">↓</div>
      <div class="chain-step chain-step-problem">
        <span class="chain-icon">💧</span>
        <strong>Excessive Diuresis → Volume Depletion</strong>
        <small>More urine than normal → circulating blood volume drops</small>
      </div>
      <div class="chain-arrow">↓</div>
      <div class="chain-step chain-step-problem">
        <span class="chain-icon">📉</span>
        <strong>Orthostatic Hypotension</strong>
        <small>BP drops sharply when rising from bed → dizziness</small>
      </div>
      <div class="chain-arrow">↓</div>
      <div class="chain-step chain-step-consequence">
        <span class="chain-icon">🚨</span>
        <strong>Mechanical Fall → Injury + Hospitalization</strong>
        <small>Right hip bruising · forearm laceration · skin integrity at risk</small>
      </div>
    </div>

    <details class="reveal-block">
      <summary>▶ Clinical Reasoning: What is orthostatic hypotension, and why are older adults especially vulnerable?</summary>
      <div class="reveal-content">
        <p><strong>Orthostatic (postural) hypotension</strong> is defined as a drop in systolic BP ≥ 20 mmHg or diastolic BP ≥ 10 mmHg within 3 minutes of standing from a sitting or lying position.</p>
        <p><strong>Why elderly patients are at increased risk:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Blunted baroreceptor reflex</strong> — aging impairs the body's ability to quickly compensate for positional BP changes</li>
          <li><strong>Reduced arterial elasticity</strong> — vessels are stiffer and cannot dilate/constrict as rapidly</li>
          <li><strong>Polypharmacy</strong> — diuretics, antihypertensives, and sedatives all compound the effect</li>
          <li><strong>Dehydration</strong> — baseline fluid intake is often lower in the elderly; kidneys are less efficient</li>
          <li><strong>Prolonged bed rest</strong> — even short periods reduce cardiovascular conditioning</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Nursing implication:</strong> Always check orthostatic vital signs before assisting Ms. Rae out of bed. Teach "dangle before standing" — sit at edge of bed for 1–2 minutes before rising.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <details class="reveal-block">
      <summary>▶ Pre-Sim Q: What intrinsic and extrinsic risk factors for falls does Ms. Rae have?</summary>
      <div class="reveal-content">
        <div class="compare-grid">
          <div>
            <h4>Intrinsic (Patient-Related) Risk Factors</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Advanced age (78 years)</li>
              <li>History of falls (fall 3 months ago)</li>
              <li>Orthostatic hypotension from medication error</li>
              <li>Urinary incontinence — urgency to reach bathroom quickly</li>
              <li>Osteoporosis — increased injury severity if fall occurs</li>
              <li>Gait and balance changes of aging</li>
              <li>Diuretic use (HCTZ) — increases urgency and nighttime toileting</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4>Extrinsic (Environmental) Risk Factors</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Getting up alone at night without assistance</li>
              <li>Hospital environment — unfamiliar layout</li>
              <li>IV tubing, Foley catheter tubing on floor</li>
              <li>Meal tray table blocking bathroom path</li>
              <li>Call light out of reach</li>
              <li>Bed in elevated position</li>
              <li>Absence of non-skid footwear</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>

  <!-- connector -->
  <div class="phase-connector">⬇ You begin your head-to-toe assessment…</div>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       PHASE 3 — ASSESSMENT FINDINGS (placeholder)
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="phase-card" id="phase3">
    <div class="phase-header">
      <span class="phase-badge">Phase 3</span>
      <h2>Assessment Findings</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="phase-intro"><em>Coming soon — Phase 3 content will appear here.</em></p>
  </div>

  <!-- Back button -->
  <div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <a href={`${base}cases/fundamentals/`} class="btn btn-back">← Back to Fundamentals</a>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ── Phase structure ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .case-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .phase-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    border-top: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
  }

  .appendix-card {
    border-top-color: var(--color-secondary);
  }

  .phase-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .phase-header h2 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  .phase-badge {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.8rem;
    border-radius: 20px;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .phase-badge-appendix {
    background: var(--color-secondary);
  }

  .phase-intro {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding-left: 0.75rem;
  }

  .phase-connector {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 0.6rem 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── Info grid ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .info-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .info-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .compare-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  .info-block h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.35rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  /* ── Tables ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .data-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .data-table th,
  .data-table td {
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    text-align: left;
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  .data-table thead th {
    background: #f0f4ff;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-primary-dark);
  }

  .data-table tbody th {
    background: #f8f9fa;
    font-weight: 600;
    width: 30%;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  /* ── Callouts ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .callout {
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .callout p { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .callout p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .callout-info {
    background: #e8f0fe;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
  }

  .callout-warning {
    background: #fff8e1;
    border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b;
  }

  .callout-danger {
    background: #fff0f0;
    border-left: 4px solid #dc2626;
  }

  .callout-success {
    background: #f0fdf4;
    border-left: 4px solid #16a34a;
  }

  /* ── Badges ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .badge-danger {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #fef2f2;
    color: #b91c1c;
    border: 1px solid #fca5a5;
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 0.1rem 0.45rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .badge-warning {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #fffbeb;
    color: #92400e;
    border: 1px solid #fde68a;
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 0.1rem 0.45rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .badge-success {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #f0fdf4;
    color: #166534;
    border: 1px solid #bbf7d0;
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 0.1rem 0.45rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* ── Scene box ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .scene-box {
    background: #f0fdf4;
    border: 1px solid #bbf7d0;
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .scene-box h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  /* ── Med list ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .med-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .med-list li {
    padding: 0.35rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .med-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  /* ── Chain flow ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .chain-flow {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0;
    margin: 1.25rem 0;
  }

  .chain-step {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 520px;
    gap: 0.2rem;
  }

  .chain-step small {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .chain-step-drug {
    background: #e8f0fe;
    color: var(--color-primary-dark);
    border: 1px solid #bfdbfe;
  }

  .chain-step-problem {
    background: #fff8e1;
    color: #78350f;
    border: 1px solid #fde68a;
  }

  .chain-step-consequence {
    background: #fef2f2;
    color: #991b1b;
    border: 1px solid #fca5a5;
  }

  .chain-arrow {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .chain-icon {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
  }

  /* ── Stat highlight ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .stat-highlight {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    background: #fef2f2;
    border: 2px solid #fca5a5;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .stat-number {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #b91c1c;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #7f1d1d;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  /* ── Reveal (details/summary) ────────────────────────────────── */
  .reveal-block {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .reveal-block > summary {
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    background: #f0f4ff;
    list-style: none;
    user-select: none;
  }

  .reveal-block > summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }

  .reveal-block[open] > summary {
    background: #dbeafe;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .reveal-block > summary:hover {
    background: #dbeafe;
  }

  .reveal-content {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
  }

  .reveal-content ul,
  .reveal-content ol {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* ── SBAR block ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .sbar-block {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .sbar-item {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
  }

  .sbar-item p { margin: 0; font-style: italic; }

  .sbar-label {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .sbar-s { background: #eff6ff; border-left: 5px solid #3b82f6; }
  .sbar-b { background: #f0fdf4; border-left: 5px solid #22c55e; }
  .sbar-a { background: #fffbeb; border-left: 5px solid #f59e0b; }
  .sbar-r { background: #fef2f2; border-left: 5px solid #ef4444; }

  /* ── Priority diagnoses ──────────────────────────────────────── */
  .dx-rank-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .dx-rank-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
    background: #f8f9fa;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
  }

  .dx-number {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 2rem;
    height: 2rem;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: #fff;
    border-radius: 50%;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .dx-aeb {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-top: 0.2rem;
  }

  /* ── Compare grid ────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .compare-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .compare-grid h4 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.35rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  /* ── Concept map ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .concept-map {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  /* ── References ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .ref-list {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .ref-note {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Utility ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .text-success { color: #15803d; }
  .text-danger  { color: #b91c1c; }

  .btn-back {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.6rem 1.4rem;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: #fff;
    border-radius: 6px;
